      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHO CAN IT BE NOW (5) wasn't disgraced in city class last time when finishing fourth at Launceston. Goes well here and was a close-up fifth only try course and distance. This easier and looks a great chance to atone. SKELMORLIE (4) didn't do a bad job when fourth last start over 1600m at Hobart, beaten 2.75 lengths after she worked home in good style. Placed 3/6 here and capable of sharp improvement. ALPINE BLAST (6) finished out of the money two starts back then he was always well out of his ground and was beaten 5 lengths when eighth in a 1350m contest at this track two weeks ago. Strong record course and distance and is expected to be in the finish. SIMPLY DEEP (3) wound up strongly to score last time and can keep the ball rolling. SCARLETTI (2) goes well course and distance and is among the chances.",
